extends ../layouts/2col.pug

block append config
  - var pageTitle = 'Progress';
  - var pageSubtitle = 'Custom progress bars featuring support for stacked bars, animated backgrounds, and text labels';
  - var skipMenu = true;

block content
  .card
    .card-body
      h3 How it works
      p Progress components are built with two HTML elements, some CSS to set the width, and a few attributes. We don't use the HTML5 <code>&lt;progress&gt;</code> element, ensuring you can stack progress bars, animate them, and place text labels over them.
      ul
        li We use the <code>.progress</code> as a wrapper to indicate the max value of the progress bar.
        li The .progress wrapper also requires a <code>role="progressbar"</code> and <code>aria</code> attributes to make it accessible, including an accessible name (using <code>aria-label</code>, <code>aria-labelledby</code>, or similar).
        li We use the inner <code>.progress-bar</code> purely for the visual bar and label.
        li The <code>.progress-bar</code> requires an inline style, utility class, or custom CSS to set its width.
        li We provide a special <code>.progress-stacked</code> class to create multiple/stacked progress bars.
      p Put that all together, and you have the following examples.

      .bd-example
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Basic example' aria-valuenow='0' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar(style='width: 0%')
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Basic example' aria-valuenow='25' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar(style='width: 25%')
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Basic example' aria-valuenow='50' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar(style='width: 50%')
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Basic example' aria-valuenow='75' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar(style='width: 75%')
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Basic example' aria-valuenow='100' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar(style='width: 100%')

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Basic example" aria-valuenow="0" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar" style="width: 0%"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Basic example" aria-valuenow="25" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar" style="width: 25%"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Basic example" aria-valuenow="50" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar" style="width: 50%"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Basic example" aria-valuenow="75" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar" style="width: 75%"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Basic example" aria-valuenow="100" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar" style="width: 100%"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;

      h3 Bar sizing
      h3 Width
      p Bootstrap provides a handful of utilities for setting width. Depending on your needs, these may help with quickly configuring the width of the <code>.progress-bar</code>.

      .bd-example
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Basic example' aria-valuenow='75' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar.w-75

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Basic example" aria-valuenow="75" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar w-75"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;

      h3 Height
      p You only set a <code>height</code> value on the <code>.progress</code> container, so if you change that value, the inner <code>.progress-bar</code> will automatically resize accordingly.

      .bd-example
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Example 1px high' aria-valuenow='25' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100' style='height: 1px')
          .progress-bar(style='width: 25%')
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Example 20px high' aria-valuenow='25' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100' style='height: 20px')
          .progress-bar(style='width: 25%')

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Example 1px high" aria-valuenow="25" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100" style="height: 1px"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar" style="width: 25%"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Example 20px high" aria-valuenow="25" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100" style="height: 20px"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar" style="width: 25%"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;

      h3 Labels
      p Add labels to your progress bars by placing text within the <code>.progress-bar</code>.

      .bd-example
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Example with label' aria-valuenow='25' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar(style='width: 25%') 25%

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Example with label" aria-valuenow="25" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar" style="width: 25%"&gt;25%&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;

      p Note that by default, the content inside the <code>.progress-bar</code> is controlled with <code>overflow: hidden</code>, so it doesn't bleed out of the bar. If your progress bar is shorter than its label, the content will be capped and may become unreadable. To change this behavior, you can use <code>.overflow-visible</code> from the overflow utilities, but make sure to also define an explicit text color so the text remains readable. Be aware though that currently this approach does not take into account color modes.

      .bd-example
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Example with label' aria-valuenow='10' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar.overflow-visible.text-dark(style='width: 10%') Long label text for the progress bar, set to a dark color

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Example with label" aria-valuenow="10" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar overflow-visible text-dark" style="width: 10%"&gt;Long label text for the progress bar, set to a dark color&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;

      h3 Backgrounds
      p Use background utility classes to change the appearance of individual progress bars.

      .bd-example
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Success example' aria-valuenow='25' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar.bg-success(style='width: 25%')
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Info example' aria-valuenow='50' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar.bg-info(style='width: 50%')
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Warning example' aria-valuenow='75' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar.bg-warning(style='width: 75%')
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Danger example' aria-valuenow='100' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar.bg-danger(style='width: 100%')

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Success example" aria-valuenow="25" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar bg-success" style="width: 25%"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Info example" aria-valuenow="50" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar bg-info" style="width: 50%"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Warning example" aria-valuenow="75" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar bg-warning" style="width: 75%"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Danger example" aria-valuenow="100" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar bg-danger" style="width: 100%"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;

      p If you're adding labels to progress bars with a custom background color, make sure to also set an appropriate text color, so the labels remain readable and have sufficient contrast.

      .bd-example
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Success example' aria-valuenow='25' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar.bg-success(style='width: 25%') 25%
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Info example' aria-valuenow='50' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar.bg-info.text-dark(style='width: 50%') 50%
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Warning example' aria-valuenow='75' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar.bg-warning.text-dark(style='width: 75%') 75%
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Danger example' aria-valuenow='100' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar.bg-danger(style='width: 100%') 100%

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Success example" aria-valuenow="25" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar bg-success" style="width: 25%"&gt;25%&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Info example" aria-valuenow="50" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar bg-info text-dark" style="width: 50%"&gt;50%&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Warning example" aria-valuenow="75" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar bg-warning text-dark" style="width: 75%"&gt;75%&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Danger example" aria-valuenow="100" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar bg-danger" style="width: 100%"&gt;100%&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;

      p Alternatively, you can use the new combined color and background helper classes.

      .bd-example
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Warning example' aria-valuenow='75' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar.text-bg-warning(style='width: 75%') 75%

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Warning example" aria-valuenow="75" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar text-bg-warning" style="width: 75%"&gt;75%&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;

      h3 Multiple bars
      p You can include multiple progress components inside a container with <code>.progress-stacked</code> to create a single stacked progress bar. Note that in this case, the styling to set the visual width of the progress bar must be applied to the <code>.progress</code> elements, rather than the <code>.progress-bar</code>s.

      .bd-example
        .progress-stacked
          .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Segment one' aria-valuenow='15' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100' style='width: 15%')
            .progress-bar
          .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Segment two' aria-valuenow='30' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100' style='width: 30%')
            .progress-bar.bg-success
          .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Segment three' aria-valuenow='20' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100' style='width: 20%')
            .progress-bar.bg-info

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;div class="progress-stacked"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Segment one" aria-valuenow="15" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100" style="width: 15%"&gt;
          |     &lt;div class="progress-bar"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          |   &lt;/div&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Segment two" aria-valuenow="30" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100" style="width: 30%"&gt;
          |     &lt;div class="progress-bar bg-success"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          |   &lt;/div&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Segment three" aria-valuenow="20" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100" style="width: 20%"&gt;
          |     &lt;div class="progress-bar bg-info"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          |   &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;

      h3 Striped
      p Add <code>.progress-bar-striped</code> to any <code>.progress-bar</code> to apply a stripe via CSS gradient over the progress bar's background color.

      .bd-example
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Default striped example' aria-valuenow='10' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar.progress-bar-striped(style='width: 10%')
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Success striped example' aria-valuenow='25' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar.progress-bar-striped.bg-success(style='width: 25%')
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Info striped example' aria-valuenow='50' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar.progress-bar-striped.bg-info(style='width: 50%')
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Warning striped example' aria-valuenow='75' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar.progress-bar-striped.bg-warning(style='width: 75%')
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Danger striped example' aria-valuenow='100' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar.progress-bar-striped.bg-danger(style='width: 100%')

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Default striped example" aria-valuenow="10" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar progress-bar-striped" style="width: 10%"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Success striped example" aria-valuenow="25" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar progress-bar-striped bg-success" style="width: 25%"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Info striped example" aria-valuenow="50" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar progress-bar-striped bg-info" style="width: 50%"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Warning striped example" aria-valuenow="75" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar progress-bar-striped bg-warning" style="width: 75%"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Danger striped example" aria-valuenow="100" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar progress-bar-striped bg-danger" style="width: 100%"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;

      h3 Animated stripes
      p The striped gradient can also be animated. Add <code>.progress-bar-animated</code> to <code>.progress-bar</code> to animate the stripes right to left via CSS3 animations.

      .bd-example
        .progress(role='progressbar' aria-label='Animated striped example' aria-valuenow='75' aria-valuemin='0' aria-valuemax='100')
          .progress-bar.progress-bar-striped.progress-bar-animated(style='width: 75%')

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;div class="progress" role="progressbar" aria-label="Animated striped example" aria-valuenow="75" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="progress-bar progress-bar-striped progress-bar-animated" style="width: 75%"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
